-- StanChart names new global M&A chief after current head Suckling goes on leave
-- 
-- Thu Apr 24, 2014 05:49AM EDT
-- None



SINGAPORE, April 24 (Reuters) - Standard Chartered <STAN.L> on Thursday named Tom Willett as its new global head of mergers and acquisitions from June 1 to replace current head Andrew Suckling, who is taking a 12-month sabbatical.

Willett joined Standard Chartered in 2012 as the bank's head of M&A for Europe from RBS <RBS.L> where he held senior positions such as chairman of corporate finance Europe, Middle East and Africa, the bank said in a statement.